Class Clause

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • java.util.ArrayList<IBooleanLiteral>
          • bits.Clause
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IClause, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>, java.lang.Iterable<IBooleanLiteral>, java.util.Collection<IBooleanLiteral>, java.util.List<IBooleanLiteral>, java.util.RandomAccess

    public class Clause
extends java.util.ArrayList<IBooleanLiteral>
implements IClause
    A class which represents a satisfiability clause. IClause is essentially an ArrayList of IBooleanLiteral objects, and additionally provides several useful methods for manipulating and evaluating the truth value of an IClause.
    Since:
    2004/08/26
    Version:
    1.01
    Author:
    Kerry Michael Soileau

    email: ksoileau2@yahoo.com

    website: http://kerrysoileau.com/index.html

      • differsSinglyFrom

        public IBooleanLiteral differsSinglyFrom(IClause c)
                                  throws java.lang.Exception
        This method returns non-null if and only if the following conditions are all true: 
         1. this.size()==c.size() 
 2. this.minus(c) contains exactly one literal 
 3. c.minus(this) contains exactly one literal 
 4. this.minus(c).getBooleanVariable()==c.minus(this).getBooleanVariable()
        Parameters:
        c - IClause
        Returns:
        IBooleanLiteral
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - An instance of Exception

      • dominates

        public boolean dominates(IClause clause)
                  throws java.lang.Exception
        An IClause A dominates an IClause B if and only if every IBooleanLiteral in A can be found in B. In that case, A & B <--> A. Practically speaking, if A dominates B, then B is redundant and may be deleted from any IProblem which includes the IClause A.
        Parameters:
        clause - IClause
        Returns:
        boolean
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - An instance of Exception

      • isTrivial

        public boolean isTrivial()
        An IClause is trivial if and only if it contains some IBooleanVariable that is barred and the same IBooleanVariable that is unbarred. This makes the IClause trivially satisfied, and makes it eligible for deletion from the IProblem in which it resides.
        Returns:
        boolean
